sentences: Arthur Schutt (November 21, 1902 – January 28, 1965) was an American jazz pianist and arranger.

He spent much of the 1940s and 1950s working in the Hollywood recording studios.
Schutt composed a jazz tune "Delirium" in 1927, which was widely recorded.
In 1934, Schutt co-wrote "Georgia Jubilee" with Benny Goodman which, while a hit, was also recorded by Isham Jones's band.
Schutt died in San Francisco, California, in January 1965, at the age of 62.
